declarations.name: AnchoredRegionAutoUpdateModeEnum
declarations.description:
Defines if the component updates its position automatically. Calling update() always provokes an update.
anchor - the component only updates its position when the anchor resizes (default)
auto - the component updates its position when:
- update() is called
- the anchor resizes
- the window resizes
- the viewport resizes
- any scroll event in the document

declarations.name: AnchoredRegionPositionLabelEnum

Depending on the axis start = left/top, end = right/bottom

declarations.description:
Some states and properties are applicable to all host language elements regardless of whether a role is applied.
The following global states and properties are supported by all roles and by all base markup elements.
declarations.name: ARIAGlobalStatesAndProperties

members.name: ariaAtomic
members.description: Indicates whether assistive technologies will present all, or only parts of, the changed region based on the change notifications defined by the `aria-relevant` attribute.

members.name: ariaBusy
members.description: Indicates an element is being modified and that assistive technologies may want to wait until the modifications are complete before exposing them to the user.

members.name: ariaControls
members.description: Identifies the element (or elements) whose contents or presence are controlled by the current element.

members.name: ariaCurrent
members.description: Indicates the element that represents the current item within a container or set of related elements.

members.name: ariaDescribedby
members.description: Identifies the element (or elements) that describes the object.

members.name: ariaDetails
members.description: Identifies the element that provides a detailed, extended description for the object.

members.name: ariaDisabled
members.description: Indicates that the element is perceivable but disabled, so it is not editable or otherwise operable.

members.name: ariaErrormessage
members.description: Identifies the element that provides an error message for the object.

members.name: ariaFlowto
members.description: Identifies the next element (or elements) in an alternate reading order of content which, at the user's discretion, allows assistive technology to override the general default of reading in document source order.

members.name: ariaHaspopup
members.description: Indicates the availability and type of interactive popup element, such as menu or dialog, that can be triggered by an element.

members.name: ariaHidden
members.description: Indicates whether the element is exposed to a screen reader.

members.name: ariaInvalid
members.description: Indicates the entered value does not conform to the format expected by the application.

members.name: ariaKeyshortcuts
members.description: Indicates keyboard shortcuts that an author has implemented to activate or give focus to an element.

members.name: ariaLabel
members.description: Defines a string value that labels the current element.

members.name: ariaLabelledby
members.description: Identifies the element (or elements) that labels the current element.

members.name: ariaLive
members.description: Indicates that an element will be updated, and describes the types of updates the user agents, assistive technologies, and user can expect from the live region.

members.name: ariaOwns
members.description: Identifies an element (or elements) in order to define a visual, functional, or contextual parent/child relationship between DOM elements where the DOM hierarchy cannot be used to represent the relationship.

members.name: ariaRelevant
members.description: Indicates what notifications the user agent will trigger when the accessibility tree within a live region is modified.

members.name: ariaRoledescription
members.description: Defines a human-readable, author-localized description for the role of an element.

members.description:
Validation state. If true, combobox is invalid.

Validation state. If true and invalid is false, combobox is in success state.

members.name: errorAriaLabel

members.name: multiple
members.description: Specifies if combobox is in multiselect mode.

members.name: closeOnSelect
members.description:
If true, listbox closes automatically on selecting an option.
If false, listbox remains open until user clicks outside or
presses escape key.

members.name: clearOnEscape
members.description: If true, when pressing escape key, combobox will emit the `clear` event.

members.name: openOnFocus
members.description: If true, upon combobox focus, listbox will open.

members.name: searchOffline
members.description:
If true, combobox will search offline in the available options.
If false, typing in the input will not filter the options. You control the filtering and the options passed to the listbox.

members.name: searchMode
members.description: Specifies search mode used when searchOffline is true.

members.name: autocomplete
members.description:
If true, on input, first option label will be populated in the field.
Works only when `searchOffline==true`, `searchMode=='startsWith'` and `multiple==false`.
To use autocomplete with a custom search mode (`searchOffline==false`), refer to the `setAutocomplete()` public method.

members.name: browserAutocomplete
members.description:
Specifies the autocomplete attribute for the input element,

members.name: virtualized
members.description: Turns virtualization feature on and off for the listbox container.

members.name: estimatedItemHeight
members.description: Default height for each option when virtualization is on.

members.name: virtualizationPadding
members.description:
Determines the number of options to render in the listbox before and after the virtualization window.
For example, if the listbox shows 7 items, and padding is 3 items, a total of 3+7+3=13 items will be rendered at a given moment.

members.name: highlightSubstrings
members.description:

that matches the user input.

members.name: resolvedFormat
members.description:
Retrieves the effective date format.

Returns the consumer-provided format if available; otherwise, falls back to the default `en-US` format.
This computed format is used when parsing default, minimum, and maximum dates.

{
	/**
	 * The tooltip is positioned above the element
	 */
	top: 'top',

	/**
	 * The tooltip is positioned above and to the right of the element
	 */
	topStart: 'top-start',

	/**
	 * The tooltip is positioned above and to the left of the element
	 */
	topEnd: 'top-end',

	/**
	 * The tooltip is positioned below the element
	 */

	bottom: 'bottom',

	/**
	 * The tooltip is positioned below and to the left of the element
	 */
	bottomStart: 'bottom-start',

	/**
	 * The tooltip is positioned below and to the right of the element
	 */
	bottomEnd: 'bottom-end',

	/**
	 * The tooltip is positioned to the right of the element
	 */
	right: 'right',

	/**
	 * The tooltip is positioned to the left of the element
	 */
	left: 'left',
}

` // File wijmo-demo.component.html

Wijmo

Choose one of the following methods to get the Saffron data-grid styles:

  1. Import stylesheets in src/styles.scss

    @use "./node_modules/@saffron/core-styles/dist/index.css";
    @use "./node_modules/@saffron/core-styles/dist/wijmo.css";

  2. Load stylesheet in angular.json

    "styles": [
    "src/styles.scss",
    "node_modules/@saffron/core-styles/dist/index.css",
    "node_modules/@saffron/core-styles/dist/wijmo.css"
    ],

Wijmo FlexGrid that has been styled with Saffron core-styles. This demo shows examples of how to approach common accessibility issues with the grid's functionality. This demo also includes custom Font Awesome icons for sorting and filtering. Default sorting is by country in descending order.
